A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Co–Location Energy Innovation and Reliability Act
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Public Service Commission to adopt regulations related
4 to the construction of a generating station that is co–located with a data center but
5 is not interconnected with the electric transmission system or electric distribution
6 system; and generally relating to the co–location of data centers with generating
7 stations.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Public Utilities
10 Section 7–207.4
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Public Utilities
16 7–207.4.
17 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
18 INDICATED.
19 (2) “CONSTRUCTION” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 7–207 OF THIS
20 SUBTITLE.
21 (3) “DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 11–239 OF THE
22 TAX – GENERAL ARTICLE.
